article.headline: Winthrop 53, Radford 52
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Marcus Cooke made two free throws with 13 seconds remaining Saturday night and Winthrop held on for a 53-52 victory against Radford. Cooke's free throws gave the Eagles (11-10, 7-5 Big South) a 53-50 lead, just enough to withstand Aaron Gill's layup for Radford with four seconds remaining. Cooke missed two more free throws with three seconds to play, but the Eagles rebounded the second miss and ran out the clock on the Highlanders (10-11, 6-5). The game was tied at 48 for over three minutes until James Shuler made a 3-pointer with 45 seconds to go. Two free throws by the Highlanders Olumuyiwa Popoola with 20 seconds left were countered by Cooke's two, setting up the final sequence. Billy Houston led Winthrop with 12 points and Shuler added 10. Popoola scored 14 points and Whit Holcomb-Faye had 10 for Radford.
